---
description: TypeScript best practices for Next.js applications to ensure type safety and maintainable code.
alwaysApply: false
---

- All API responses must be typed with TypeScript interfaces or types.
- All TypeScript code must pass strict type checking (strict: true in tsconfig).
- Use proper type annotations for all variables, parameters, and return values.
- Prefer interfaces over types for object shapes.
- Use utility types (Partial, Pick, Omit) when appropriate.
- Avoid using `any` type; use `unknown` or proper typing instead.
- Use const assertions for immutable data.
- Implement proper error handling with typed error objects.